<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Slender annual herb, usually branched at base with decumbent or ascending branches, glabrous or with a few scattered hairs; stems to 2 m long but usually much less. Leaves petiolate, small, 0.7-2.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 cm, variably palmatisect with 5-7 separate leaflets, the laterals pedate, leaflets 1-2.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.1-0.2 cm, linear-oblong, apiculate, glabrous or with a few scattered hairs; petioles 0.2-3 cm. Flowers solitary (rarely paired), axillary, pedunculate; peduncles slender, 1.8- 5 cm, straight; bracteoles 1-2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.25 mm, filiform, scarious-margined; pedicels 7-25 mm; sepals subequal, lanceolate to ovate, acute, mucronate, the mucro c. 1 mm long, glabrous or nearly so, margins scarious, outer 3-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, often muricate along prominent midrib, inner up to 6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3 mm; corolla 1-1.2 cm long, funnel-shaped, purplish, glabrous. Capsules 4-5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4 mm, globose to ovoid, glabrous, the slender style somewhat persistent; seeds 3-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2 mm, black, minutely tomentellous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
